---
import LessonLayout from '../../layouts/LessonLayout.astro';
---
<LessonLayout
  title="Robot Celebration!"
  track="little-explorers"
  week={12}
  phase="Phase 4: Mini Projects"
  duration="30 min"
  emoji="🎉"
  objective="Celebrate 12 weeks of robotics exploration together"
>
  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-explorer-700 mb-3">🎯 Learning Objective</h2>
    <p class="bg-explorer-50 border-l-4 border-explorer-400 p-4 rounded-r-xl text-gray-700">
      Reflect on everything learned, celebrate achievements, and spark excitement for what comes next in your robotics journey!
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">🛠️ Materials</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ Party snacks 🎈</li>
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ All the drawings and notes from the 12 weeks</li>
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ A special "Robot Explorer" certificate (print the template below!)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">📋 Activity Steps</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Memory Walk (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Look at all the things you made together. Your child narrates: "This is from when we did..." For each week, share one favourite memory.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Final Performance (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Run Reachy's BEST routine — the one your child is most proud of. One final time, with an audience!</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Certificate & Dreams (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Print and present the Robot Explorer certificate. Ask: "What do you want Reachy to learn next?"</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💻 Code Snippet</h2>
    <pre is:raw class="bg-gray-900 text-green-300 rounded-xl p-5 overflow-x-auto text-sm leading-relaxed"><code># celebration.py — Week 12: Little Explorers
import time

class ReachyMock:
    def celebrate(self, name):
        print(f"🎉 Reachy says:")
        print(f"   Congratulations, {name}!")
        time.sleep(0.5)
        print("   You are now a ROBOT EXPLORER!")
        time.sleep(0.5)
        print("   We learned SO much together!")
        time.sleep(0.5)
        for _ in range(3):
            print("   🤖 *happy dance* 🤖")
            time.sleep(0.3)
        print("   Thank you for being my friend! 💙")

try:
    from reachy_mini import ReachyMini
    robot = ReachyMini()
except Exception:
    robot = ReachyMock()

# Change to your child's name!
explorer_name = "Little Explorer"
robot.celebrate(explorer_name)</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8 bg-yellow-50 border-2 border-yellow-300 rounded-2xl p-6">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-yellow-700 mb-3">🏆 Robot Explorer Certificate</h2>
    <div class="border-4 border-yellow-400 rounded-xl p-6 text-center bg-white">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🤖⭐🤖</div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-extrabold mb-2">Certificate of Achievement</h3>
      <p class="text-lg mb-2">This certifies that</p>
      <div class="border-b-2 border-gray-400 w-48 mx-auto mb-2 h-8"></div>
      <p class="text-lg mb-4">has completed the</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-explorer-600 mb-4">Little Explorers 12-Week Robotics Curriculum</p>
      <p class="text-gray-600">and is now officially a Robot Explorer!</p>
      <div class="text-3xl mt-4">🌟 🤝 🌟</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💬 Reflection Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-yellow-800">🌟 "What was the BEST moment of the whole 12 weeks?"</p></div>
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-yellow-800">🌟 "What do you want to build or program next?"</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">👪 Parent Tips</h2>
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-5 text-gray-700">
      <p>💡 You just spent 12 weeks exploring robotics together. That shared experience is the real achievement — more than any code or robot move.</p>
      <p class="mt-2">💡 Consider: Young Builders track next? Or check out the other robo-kids projects!</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</LessonLayout>
